records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cindy J Wadd in court with attorney Craig Michael Kuhary.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to count # 1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. Counts #2 and #3 are dismissed and read in. Count #4 is dismissed by operation of law. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Kuhary makes statements regarding sentencing. David W. makes statement.  Defendant makes Statements.

COUNT#1:
The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE:   

*D/L REVOCATION: 48 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 48 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed, sign releases. 
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.


BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $24 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to City of Brookfield Police Department);

FINE :  $3801.00 + $250 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($1000.00) remainder paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  210 DAYS (1 DAY CREDIT)  NON WORKING HOURS, COMMENCING FORTHWITH. Defendant taken into custody. 

Victim Impact Panel on:  Completed on 02/18/15 . 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
